TITLE: Searching Google with googlethis in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to perform a Google search using the `googlethis` library in JavaScript. It showcases setting up search options like page number, safe search, parsing ads, and custom parameters. The response from the Google search is then logged to the console.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/google-this/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// const google = require('googlethis');
import google from 'googlethis';

const options = {
  page: 0, 
  safe: false, // Safe Search
  parse_ads: false, // If set to true sponsored results will be parsed
  additional_params: { 
    // add additional parameters here, see https://moz.com/blog/the-ultimate-guide-to-the-google-search-parameters and https://www.seoquake.com/blog/google-search-param/
    hl: 'en' 
  }
}

const response = await google.search('TWDG', options);
console.log(response); 
```

