TITLE: Performing Image and Reverse Image Search with googlethis
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to perform both a regular image search and a reverse image search using the `googlethis` library in JavaScript. It utilizes the `google.image` function for a standard image search with a provided search term and utilizes `google.search` with the `ris: true` option for reverse image search, taking an image file as input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/google-this/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// const google = require('googlethis');
import google from 'googlethis';

// Image Search
const images = await google.image('The Wolf Among Us', { safe: false });
console.log(images);

// Reverse Image Search
const my_awesome_image = fs.readFileSync('./wow.png');
const reverse = await google.search(my_awesome_image, { ris: true });

console.log(reverse.results);
```

